oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Golden West Cowboys (proof)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Golden West Cowboys (Musical group); King, Pee Wee, 1914-2000;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two color fragment (blue and orange on white) announcing the Golden West Cowboys. It is possible that this fragment is a hand drawn egg tempera proof. A note written in pencil over the "the" says, "J. L. Frank's original famous." JL Frank was the Golden West Cowboy's promoter.
